		<div id="overview">
			<h2>Overview</h2>
			<span itemprop="image">
				<%= image_tag("/attachments/nutrition.jpeg", alt: "Shooloo healthy eating math story contest", style: "float: right; margin-left: 1em; border-radius: 5px;", title: "Shooloo healthy eating math story contest") %>
			</span>
			<p> Nearly 1 in 3 children aged 2-19 in the United States is overweighed or obese. Unhealthy eating is the top contributor to childhood obesity. For young consumers to properly interpret nutrition labels and choose truly healthy food, they need in-depth knowledge in mathematics, including fractions, ratios, and proportional relationships.</p>
			<p>To promote nutritional awareness among children, Shooloo.org is hosting a healthy eating math story contest from May 2 to August 15, 2014. Students and teachers in grades 3-12 are invited to submit on Shooloo their own math <%= link_to "questions", posts_path %> regarding eating choices, conduct research, gather data, and devise solutions.</p> 
		</div> 
