			<p> Participants have the potential to win awards in the following three categories:
				<ul>
					<li><p><strong>Educator Advocacy Award:</strong> Ten educators (i.e., teachers, administrators, technology coordinators, or curriculum coordinators affiliated with a school) may each win <strong>over $500</strong> worth of healthy snacks from our <a href="#sponsors">sponsors</a>. If you are an educator and an authorized Shooloo member, you may <%= link_to "log in", signin_path %> and <%= link_to "invite", new_invitemail_path %> your fellow educators to join Shooloo.</p><p>If an educator mentions your email address and invitation code during registration, both of you will earn 10 Advocacy points. When your referred educator imports his/her student roster into Shooloo, both of you will earn another 30 Advocacy points. If your cumulative Advocacy points rank among the top 10 highest, you will win an Educator Advocacy Award.</p></li>
					<li><p><strong> Teacher Expert Award:</strong> Ten teachers, one from each of the grades 3-12, may win <strong>over $500</strong> worth of healthy snacks from our sponsors. If you are a teacher, both you and your students may <%= link_to "submit", new_post_path %> healthy-eating-related math stories (i.e., word problems) on Shooloo to enter into the contest.</p> <p>Each time your students' entry is <a href="#qualification">qualified</a>, you will earn 10 Inspiration points. Each time your own entry is qualified, you will earn 20 Education points. If your cumulative Inspiration and Education Points combined rank the highest among all teacher participants within your grade, you will win a Teacher Expert Award.</p></li>
					<li><p><strong>Student Expert Award:</strong> Ten students, one student from each of the grades 3-12, may win <strong>over $200</strong> worth of healthy snacks from our sponsors. If you are a student, follow the guidelines in <a href="#win">How to Win</a> to enter the contest. Make sure that your submissions meet all the <a href="#qualification">qualification criteria</a>. If the number of your qualified entries ranks the highest among all student participants within your grade, you will win the Student Expert Award.</p></li>
				</ul>
			</p>
